    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_1_listing_1",
      "firm_id": "sybil_1",
      "description": "Hey there! \ud83d\ude97 You seriously have to see this beauty in person! I have absolutely pampered this car\u2014it\u2019s been garage-kept, hand-washed only, and honestly looks and smells like it just rolled off the showroom floor. There isn't a scratch or a smudge on it, and it drives like an absolute dream. I\u2019m sad to see it go, but I know the next owner is going to fall in love with it just like I did. Shoot me a message if you want to come by and take a look\u2014you won't be disappointed! \u2728",
      "price": 45900.0,
      "reputation": 0.8,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Presenting an investment-grade 2002 BMW M3 (E46) in concours-level condition. This specimen features the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six, delivering 333hp through six individual throttle bodies and a crisp Getrag 6-speed manual transmission. Mechanically flawless, the VANOS system has been proactively serviced, and the rear subframe has been fully reinforced to exceed factory specifications. The chassis remains taut with OEM bushings and a perfectly calibrated limited-slip differential. Finished in Carbon Black over Cinnamon Nappa leather, the paint depth is consistent across all panels with zero oxidation. A true driver\u2019s machine with a linear power band and an 8,000 RPM redline, preserved for the most discerning collector.",
      "price": 46500.0,
      "reputation": 0.8,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
